> Get this hearty, comforting bowl of creamy deliciousness on the table in just 25 minutes!

Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches; bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Drain and set aside.

While potatoes cook, cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Place broccoli and 2 TBSP water in a #large microwave-safe bowl{}; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Carefully remove plastic wrap and drain.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites, garlic, and @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @cheese roux concentrate{1%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, and 2 cups water. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir broccoli, potatoes, @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, and half the @Dijon mustard{2%tsp} into same pot until fully combined and cheese is incorporated. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

> TIP: If your potatoes aren't finished cooking yet, just stir them in when they're tender.

Remove from heat.

Divide soup between bowls; garnish with scallion greens. Serve.